Purple works well in a well-lit room as it absorbs light, especially if using a dark shade. Use plenty of white to brighten up the mood and add a crispy freshness to this luxurious colour. ALSO READ:

Creating a classy bachelor's pad Purple and green can be used in a master bedroom where the femininity of purple can be balanced by a soothing citrus green. The green breaks the monotony of the purple and makes the combination suitable for both sexes. Pair purple with a bright yellow to make a lively colour statement. These colours make interesting bedfellows as the scheme shows how complementary colours can bring out the best in each other. 